"VZLUSAT-2 is a technological mission that should verify several subsystems for more advanced future missions. Many technologies are being tested in the Czech Republic for the first time. Despite advanced simulation and testing possibilities, it is not possible to fully verify everything here on Earth, so we need to obtain data from the orbit, this applies for example to the precise attitude control system that cannot be fully verified here on Earth.‚Äú Notes the head of VZL√ö satellite systems Juraj Dud√°≈°. 

